{"id":56349,"title":"Flashes and floaters - a practical approach to assessment and management.","abstract":"Flashes and floaters are common ophthalmic issues for which patients may initially present to their general practitioner. It may be a sign of benign, ?age-related changes of the vitreous or more serious retinal detachment.This article provides a guide to the assessment and management of a patient presenting with flashes and floaters.Although most patients presenting with flashes and floaters have benign ?age-related changes, they must be referred to an ophthalmologist to rule out sight-threatening conditions. Key examination features include the nature of the flashes and floaters, whether one or both eyes are affected and changes in visual acuity or visual field.","date":"2014-04-04","categories":"Eye Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24701623","annotations":[{"name":"Retinal detachment","weight":0.877753,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Retinal_detachment"},{"name":"Ophthalmology","weight":0.829201,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ophthalmology"},{"name":"Visual acuity","weight":0.791501,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_acuity"},{"name":"General practitioner","weight":0.469348,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_practitioner"},{"name":"Vitreous humour","weight":0.42481,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vitreous_humour"},{"name":"Visual field","weight":0.410802,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_field"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.306173,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Visual system","weight":0.258256,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_system"},{"name":"Retinal","weight":0.256854,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Retinal"},{"name":"Detachment","weight":0.218004,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Detachment"},{"name":"Floater","weight":0.116096,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Floater"},{"name":"Medical sign","weight":0.067811,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_sign"},{"name":"Nature","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nature"},{"name":"Test (assessment)","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test_(assessment)"},{"name":"Field (mathematics)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Field_(mathematics)"},{"name":"Flash (comics)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flash_(comics)"},{"name":"Obstetrics","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Obstetrics"},{"name":"Evaluation","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evaluation"},{"name":"General officer","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_officer"},{"name":"Key (company)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Key_(company)"},{"name":"Benignity","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benignity"},{"name":"Management","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Management"}]}
